Greetings to Zambian President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, on Oct. 22 sent a message of greetings to Levy Patrick Mwanawasa, President of Zambia, on the occasion of the 43rd anniversary of its independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Expressing the belief that the excellent friendly and cooperative relations between the two countries would grow stronger in the interests of the two peoples in the future, too, the message wished the Zambian president success in his work for national unity and sustainable economic development.

Japan's Militarist Moves for Overseas Expansion under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- The Japanese reactionaries' attempt to completely legalize the advance of the Japan "Self-Defense Forces (SDF)" overseas comes under fire by a signed commentary of Minju Joson Tuesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Liberal Democratic Party of Japan is busy working out a new bill calling for extending the "law on special measures against terrorism" as it is expected to expire on Nov. 1 this year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to the bill the drafting of which is almost completed, the LDP laid down the principle calling for limiting the Maritime SDF's logistic activities in the Indian Ocean to supply of oil and drinking water to warships of other countries and not supplying oil to supply ships of the U.S. carrier due to the suspicion that the oil supply to the carrier might be diverted to the purpose of operations against Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, opposition parties have taken a fresh step in this respect by asserting that Japan should stop oil supply in the Indian Ocean and join, instead, in the military activities of the NATO-led international security volunteers in Afghanistan. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Judging from the assertions of the ruling and opposition parties of Japan, it is clear that they share the same view that it is necessary to quickly lay a legal foundation for military activities of the SDF overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is sheer nonsense for Japan to claim that it stands for overseas advance because the SDF is interested in the peace and humanitarian activities overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the calculation of the Japanese reactionaries that Japan can neither increase its influence and say in settling international issues nor secure a hegemonic position in the region, in particular, as long as the SDF is detained inside the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 For this reason, they are keen to boost the SDF's military capability to the maximum and send its beefed-up troops overseas in a bid not to lose the chance to meddle in international affairs but bring the Asian region under their military control. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is evidenced by the facts that Japan is contemplating staging test-firing interceptor missile SM-3 mounted on Aegis "Kongo" in the waters off Hawaii in December and busying itself with the moves to make a legislation for the advance of the SDF overseas. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This tells that Japan's militarist moves for overseas expansion have reached a very serious stage and they are fraught with potential danger. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Japan's overseas expansion after emerging a military giant precisely means a war, warns the commentary.

Foreign Delegations Here 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- A delegation of the European Parliament headed by Hubert Pirker, chairman of the Delegation for the Relations with Korean Peninsula, arrived here Tuesday to participate in the DPRK-European Union economic symposium to be held here. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also arriving here on the same day were a delegation of the Party School of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China led by Education Director Li Xingshan and a delegation of the Vietnam General Confederation of Labor headed by Senior Vice-President Nguyen Hoa Binh.

Polish Sports Poster Exhibition Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- A Polish sports poster exhibition was held at the Pyongyang International House of Culture from Oct. 18 to 23 on the occasion of the Independence Day of Poland. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@On display there were more than 40 posters showing the history of sports development in Poland. Among them were "The First All-Poland's Academic Games 1921," "The 13th International Bicycle Peace Race Prague, Warsaw, Berlin 1960," "The 4th All-Poland's Athletic Meeting 1967" and "The Ski Jumping World Cup, Zakopane 2006." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The exhibition marked an occasion in furthering the friendly relations between the peoples of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and Poland.

U.S. Reckless Arms Buildup under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- The director of the Missile Defense Agency of the U.S. Defense Department blustered some days ago that the U.S. moves to set up the missile defense system (MD) are aimed at coping with the "threat from such rogue states as north Korea." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Tuesday in a signed commentary carried in this regard observes that his outbursts were prompted by the U.S. sinister plan to bolster the preemptive attack forces of the U.S. troops in and around the Korean Peninsula and thus provoke the second Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Recalling that the U.S. bellicose forces have amassed sophisticated military hardware and war means in and around the peninsula, the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is in pursuance of the above-said plan that the department has recently deployed mobile missile chasing equipment for the first time in Japan, raising a hue and cry over "missile threat" from the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Timed to coincide with this move, the department transferred KC-135 and four B-2s to the Anderson U.S. air-force base in Guam from its mainland and it began deploying F-16s of improved version in its air-force bases in south Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces are asserting that these military moves are aimed at countering the DPRK's moves to bolster its missile forces. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This is, however, nothing but sheer sophism intended to justify their arms build-up escalated to start a war under the non-existent "missile threat" from the DPRK. In escalating their campaigns to isolate and pressurize the DPRK, the U.S. bellicose forces seek to take a physical option against it if their gangster-like demand lurking behind their loudmouthed "peace" and "dialogue" does not work on it. But such U.S. double-dealing tactics can never go down with the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. frantic moves to establish the MD are creating a dangerous situation in and around the Korean Peninsula where the military equilibrium may be upset and a new arms race may rage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. would be well advised to see through the seriousness and danger of the present situation and stop at once its reckless and adventurous moves for a war against the DPRK.

New Species of Cardamine Flexuosa Found 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- The research institute under the Central Botanical Garden has recently found a new species of Cardamine flexuosa which belongs to Cruciferae while surveying plants in Mt. Myohyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
Cardamine flexuosa, distributed in different parts of the Northern Hemisphere, grows 10-30 cm high. According to records, there are more than 100 species of Cardamine flexuosa in the world and 14 species in Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The new species, which was found for the first time in the world, forms a plant community in Chilsong-dong of Mt. Myohyang. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to Jo Yong Gil, a section chief of the research institute, the morphological character of the new species is that it is 30-40 cm tall, two to three compound leaves grow from its stem and its flower is larger than those of other species. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Researchers of the institute had found a new species belonging to the rhododendron family for the first time in the world while surveying plants in Mt. Paektu two years ago, thus contributing to proving a rich biodiversity in the region.

New Koryo Treatment Methods Introduced  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- The Academy of Koryo Medical Science has researched and applied new Koryo treatment methods to improving people's health. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Its researchers have deepened the research into Koryo treatment methods suitable to the way of life and constitutional features of the Koreans in relation with modern medical science. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Especially they have positively introduced the therapies by needle, moxibustion and massage and the combinational therapy by injection for local incurable disease with cupping for the treatment of patients. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Very high is the complete cure rate by such superior traditional treatment methods as cure of the advanced stomach cancer and intervertebral disk extrusion in combination with Koryo medicines and the cure method by rare-earth moxibustion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@They have also developed various kinds of Koryo medicines good for health to widely apply them to the treatment. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Academy of Koryo Medical Science has made traditional Koryo medicines with plants abundant in Korea, which are efficacious for the treatment of various diseases including cardiovascular disease. They have found out the efficacy of the medicines through experimental research in a scientific way and are applying them to clinical practice.

Boxing Contests for Title and Play-off of WBCF Held 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- Boxing contests for title and play-off of the World Boxing Council of Female (WBCF) took place in Kaesong on Oct. 19 under the sponsorship of the WBCF. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The contests were watched by Ri Yong Son, minister of Commerce, who is chairman of the Korean Boxing Association, officials in the field of physical culture and sports, sportspersons, boxing fans and working people in Kaesong. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Pak Sang Gwon, president of the WBCF, and its members and compatriots from the south were among the spectators. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK boxer Ryu Myong Ok played ten rounds for two minutes with her Mexican rival Ana Maria Torres, champion of the category, to win the super fly class (52.16 kg) title. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ryu defeated her rival 2:1 decision at the tenth round, grabbing the title. A champion's girdle, trophy and certificate went to Ryu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Matches for play-offs in different categories took place on the same day, each with six rounds for two minutes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 DPRK boxer Ryu Yong Sim knocked down her south Korean rival Choe Sin Hui in the bantamweight (53.52 kg) match in one minute and 46 seconds from its start. Yang Ye Ok of the DPRK trounced her Japanese rival Tsubasa at super fly class (52.16 kg) match 3:0 and Kim Hye Song of the DPRK beat her south Korean rival Pak Ji Hyon at fly class (50.80 kg) event 3:0. They were thus qualified to participate in the next contests for play-offs. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, Jang Song Ae of the DPRK knocked down her Japanese rival Anri Nakagawa in one minute and 15 seconds at the minimum class (47.61 kg) match. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Trophies were awarded to Ryu Yong Sim, Yang Ye Ok, Kim Hye Song and Jang Song Ae each. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the contests, men's amateur boxing matches took place between boxers from the north and the south of Korea.

Kim Jong Il Praised in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- The South Headquarters of the National Alliance of Youth and Students for the Country's Reunification posted an article praising the personality of Kim Jong Il as a great man and his imperishable revolutionary feats on its Internet homepage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article in its preface noted that a furious "hot wind of Kim Jong Il" has been sweeping south Korea since the historic Pyongyang meeting in 2000. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It consists of "Distinguished Endowments of Chairman of the National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il", "Revolutionary Activities of Chairman of the National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il Acclaimed as Successor" and "Chairman of the National Defence Commission Kim Jong Il Turns 'Arduous March' into Journey of Happiness." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The article in its first part dealt with Kim Jong Il's revolutionary activities from his childhood to his university days. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the second part it told about the immortal contributions he has made to the country and the revolution by leading the Party, the army and the people with his brilliant wisdom and outstanding leadership ability since he started his work at the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the third part it elaborated on the fact that he surmounted mounting troubles with his Songun leadership in the grim period when the DPRK was forced to make "an arduous march" by the strong-arm and arbitrary practices of the United States which became all the more wanton and unprecedented manifold natural disasters and economic difficulties in the 1990s. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The people in the south living in an era of reconciliation and unity, not in an era of confrontation and division, should know well about the personality of Kim Jong Il as a great man leading the society of the north for the common prosperity of the nation, the article said, adding: This is logical necessity for an early reunification of the country.

Anniversary of WPK Observed in Foreign Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- A friendship meeting, round-table talks and an art performance were held in Laos, Bulgaria and the Czech Republic from Oct. 8 to 11 on the occasion of the 62nd founding anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On display in the venues of the functions were photos showing the immortal exploits of President Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Khamphan Sittidampha, secretary of the Central Committee of the Lao People's Revolutionary Youth Union, at a friendship meeting, said that the Workers' Party of Korea is a model of the world progressive political parties. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Watching the scenes showing the recent external activities of Kim Jong Il, he said he learned well about the greatness of his leadership art steering the world politics. The WPK guided by the great leader would always emerge victorious, he added. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Vasilka Nikiforova, chief of "Kim Il Sung Library" in Sofia of Bulgaria, and Maria Nikiforova, secretary general of the Bulgaria-Korea Friendship Association, at the round-table talks highly praised the immortal feats of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The editor-in-chief of the newspaper Dialog of the Czech Republic at the round-table talks referred in detail to the exploits performed by Kim Il Sung in party building. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dwelling on the originality and great vitality of the Songun politics, he stressed that the Workers' Party of Korea and the Korean people led by Kim Jong Il would win one victory after another. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The repertoire of the art performance given in Laos included Korean songs "Our General Is Best" and "Let Us Defend Socialism".

Special Write-ups Posted on Foreign Internet Homepages on WPK's Birthday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 23 (KCNA) -- A political party, institution and organizations of different countries posted special write-ups on their Internet homepages in the period from Oct. 6 to 9 to mark the 62nd anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Brazilian Communist Party in an article posted on its Internet homepage introduced in detail the proud course covered by the WPK for the last 62 years since its foundation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The SANA of Syria posted on its Internet homepage a portrait of leader Kim Jong Il and a picture of a flag of the DPRK along with an article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is entirely attributable to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il that the WPK has led the people to defend the sovereignty of the country and registered spectacular successes internally and externally, the article noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The German Group for the Study of Songun Politics posted on its Internet homepage photos showing the revolutionary activities of Kim Jong Il and a CD dealing with the Songun revolutionary feats of the peerlessly great persons and introducing the struggle of the Korean people as well as articles titled "Principle of Songun revolution" and "Socialist construction stepped up on the principle of Songun".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Peruvian Group for the Study of Kimilsungism posted an article praising the party leadership feats of Kim Jong Il on its Internet homepage.

Minju Joson denuncia maniobras expansionistas de Japon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de octubre (ATCC) -- El rotativo Minju Joson publico en su edicion de hoy un comentario individual con respecto a que en estos dias los reaccionarios japoneses intentan legitimar la salida a ultramar de las "fuerzas de autodefensa". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
   El Partido Democratico Liberal de Japon se enfrasca en elaborar un nuevo "proyecto de ley" para dar prorroga a la "ley de medidas especiales frente al terrorismo", que va a vencer el primero de noviembre que viene. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Segun ese proyecto casi completado, el PDLJ propone el principio de limitar las actividades de las "fuerzas navales de autodefensa" en el Oceano Indico al suministro de combustibles y agua potable a los barcos extranjeros excepto la nave nodriza para el portaaviones estadounidense, dado que se levantaron las sospechas de que este ultimo buque haya tomado parte en las operaciones contra Iraq. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  En tanto, en un gesto mas inteligente, los partidos opositores insisten en el paro del suministro de combustibles en el Oceano Indico y en tomar parte en el Ejercito Internacional para la Seguridad de Afganistan al mando de la OTAN. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Como insinuan sus criterios, tanto el partido gobernante como los opositores coinciden en que se debe preparar con rapidez una base legal para las actividades militares de las "fuerzas de autodefensa" en ultramar. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Es una pura mentira que las "fuerzas de autodefensa" del pais isleno desean salir a ultramar por estar interesadas en la paz y las actividades humanitarias en el extranjero. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Los reaccionarios japoneses creen que si mantienen inactivas a esas fuerzas en el pais, no podran aumentar la influencia y el derecho a la palabra de su pais en los problemas internacionales ni garantizar la posicion hegemonica en la region. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Aumentan al maximo la capacidad militar de las "fuerzas de autodefensa" y envian a ultramar a los efectivos de exceso a fin de intervenir rapidamente en los problemas internacionales y tomar el control militar en la region asiatica. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Para este fin, intentan embarcar en el barco Aegis "Kongo" los misiles "SM-3" y realizar el lanzamiento de ensayo de misil antibalistico en el mar frente a Hawai. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Todos los hechos demuestran que el expansionismo militarista de Japon llega a una etapa muy grave adquiriendo la peligrosidad real. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La expansion a ultramar de Japon, convertido en una potencia militar, significa la guerra.

Rodong Sinmun denuncia aumento armamentista de EE.UU.
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 23 de octubre (ATCC) -- Ultimamente, el director de la Agencia de Defensa Antimisil del Departamento de Defensa norteamericano dijo que el establecimiento del sistema antimisiles de EE.UU. es para hacer frente a la "amenaza de los Estados bribones como el Norte de Corea".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Se trata del designio de fortalecer las fuerzas de ataque preventivo de las tropas norteamericanas en la Peninsula Coreana y en su contorno y desatar luego la segunda guerra coreana. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Asi senala el diario Rodong Sinmun en un comentario individual del dia 23 y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La capa belicosa norteamericana ubica de modo concentrado los pertrechos militares modernos y los medios belicos en la Peninsula Coreana y su periferia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Como su colofon, el Departamento de Defensa norteamericano, al hablar de la "amenaza de misiles" de la Republica Popular Democratica de Corea, instalo por primera vez en Japon el aparato movil de persecucion de misil. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Coincidiendo en tiempo con esto, el Departamento de Defensa norteamericano traslado de su territorio a la base aerea Andersen de la isla Guam la nodriza aerea "KC-135" y 4 bombarderos estrategicos de larga distancia "B-2" y comenzo a ubicar en su base  aerea situada en el Sur de Corea el caza "F-16".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La capa belicosa norteamericana alega que tal medida militar es para "hacer frente" al fortalecimiento de la capacidad misilistica de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Esto no pasa de ser una sofisteria gangsteril para justificar el aumento armamentista tendente a provocar nueva guerra so pretexto de la "amenaza de misiles" de la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  La fuerza belicista norteamericana, al aumentar el grado de aislamiento y presion sobre la RPDC, trata de aplicar el metodo fisico en caso de que no surta efecto su bandidesca demanda escondida detras del telon de "paz" y "dialogo". Pero tal artimana de doble rasero de EE.UU. no surtira efecto para con la RPDC. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Por las freneticas maniobras de establecimiento del sistema antimisiles de EE.UU., se crea el peligro de que se destruya el equilibrio militar y se desate una nueva carrera armamentista en la Peninsula Coreana y su periferia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  EE.UU. debe justipreciar la gravedad y la peligrosidad de la situacion actual y poner de inmediato fin a tal aventurera maniobra belica anti- RPDC.
